## Ship docs/ in Databricks deploy bundle for Help Center

Context: The in-app Help Center lists documentation from a hardcoded catalog
but serves markdown from `docs/` on disk. `.databricksignore` and `databricks.yml`
previously excluded the entire `docs/` tree (and all `*.md`), so every
`/api/help/docs/{slug}` call returned HTTP 404 in deployed Databricks Apps —
including Product.

Changes:

1. `.databricksignore`
   Include `docs/` for Help Center runtime; exclude Sphinx `_build/` output and
   root/repo-meta markdown only (no blanket `*.md` / `*.txt`).
2. `databricks.yml`
   Add explicit `docs/**` sync include; replace blanket `docs/` + `*.md`
   excludes with targeted root markdown and Sphinx build exclusions.
3. `docs/deployment.md`
   Document that `docs/` is now shipped for in-app Help Center support.

Modified files:
- `.databricksignore`
- `databricks.yml`
- `docs/deployment.md`
- `changelogs/v0.4.0/2026-05-26.log`

Tests: uv run pytest -q → 2337 passed in 435.64s

