## Fix empty mapping attribute dropdown for OWL-generated classes

Context: In Mapping → Mapping tab, clicking a SQL column header opens a menu
with ID/Label plus ontology attributes. RadioCell showed "No attributes" while
the SQL preview had many columns. The OWL generator often declares datatype
properties via owl:Restriction on the class without rdfs:domain; OntologyParser
only collected attributes from rdfs:domain, so classes loaded with empty
dataProperties.

Changes:

1. `src/back/core/w3c/owl/OntologyParser.py`
   Also derive class dataProperties from owl:Restriction axioms (including
   intersectionOf lists with blank-node members).
2. `src/back/objects/ontology/Ontology.py`
   Add sync/finalize helpers to merge datatype properties onto classes after
   OWL ingest.
3. `src/back/objects/session/DomainSession.py`
   Finalize class attributes on every domain load/migration.
4. `src/front/static/ontology/js/ontology-information.js`
   Merge parser and domain-based attributes when importing OWL in the UI.
5. `src/agents/agent_owl_generator/engine.py`
   Require rdfs:domain on DatatypeProperty in the generator prompt.
6. `tests/units/ontology/test_owl_parser.py`
   Regression test for restriction-only datatype properties.

Modified files:
- `src/back/core/w3c/owl/OntologyParser.py`
- `src/back/objects/ontology/Ontology.py`
- `src/back/objects/session/DomainSession.py`
- `src/front/static/ontology/js/ontology-information.js`
- `src/agents/agent_owl_generator/engine.py`
